Evolution of economic
Classical period of 
economic theory
• In order to understand the evolution of neuroeconomics we 
have to go back to the evolution of economic
• The birth of economic is often traced to Adam Smith’s 
publication of The Wealth of Nations in 1776. Smith described a 
number of phenomena critical for understanding choice 
behavior (e.g. how characteristics of the environment 
influenced the behavior of consumers and producers).
Basic concepts: 
• wealth of any nation was determined by national income (and 
not monarch’s gold!!), 
• Income is based on the labor 
• Labor organized efficiently by the division of labor
• Theory of value (of exchange)
• Introduction of different 
concepts:
• Value
• Price
• Cost

