Normative Decision making theories
• Normative decision theory is concerned with identification of 
optimal decisions where optimality is often determined by 
considering an ideal decision maker who is able to calculate with 
perfect accuracy and is in some sense fully rational.

---PAGE---

Descriptive Decision makingtheories
• In contrast, positive or descriptive decision theory is concerned with 
describing observed behaviors often under the assumption that the 
decision-making agents are behaving under some consistent rules.

