This is the basic of the fMRI method.
The blood vessels of our brain carry O2 to neurons. 
When neurons are active (e.g. during a mental 
activity) specific brain regions require hemoglobin, 
that carries O2.
Hemoglobin changes the magnetic properties of 
brain tissues and these changes can be detected by a 
scanner. Thus, the scanner detect the BOLD signal. 

